sections.heading: Contempt; punishment; effect on other proceedings
sections.text: Punishment for contempt, as provided in sections 50-105 to 50-109, is no bar to any other proceedings, civil or criminal, for the same offense.SourceR.S.1866, c. 31, § 12, p. 251;R.S.1913, § 3751;C.S.1922, § 3144;C.S.1929, § 50-110;R.S.1943, § 50-110
